 Khumalo, who was in a customary marriage to Kubheka for the past 10 years, was horrified to learn that her late husband had sired 24 children.This came to her attention when Kubheka's children, a group of about 14 kids, were called to climb onto the podium during her hubby's memorial service last week.On the day of the funeral, 10 more kids were introduced during the service in Soweto, south of Jozi.Khumalo said that she only knew of four kids, their first born, two from his previous marriage and one from Durban.TO READ THE FULL STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD AT YOUR NEAREST STORE 